        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 3:23PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 323 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 3
miles south of Black Hawk, or 3 miles northwest of Rapid City, moving
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rapid City, Black Hawk, and Summerset.

This includes Interstate 90 in South Dakota between Mile Markers 51
and 62.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
